column5: Assuming normal summer water levels can a 16 foot 50hp fishing boat travel from Kashagawigamog to the connecting lakes? Soyers, Grass. Head?
Thanks for the feedback. Looking to spend a week there this summer.
Booked for the last week in July. Fun family time at the lake.
Busy lake, but the narrows into Soyers makes that lake a bit quieter!
that's a good choice, yeah, it's a busy circus, but there's lots of water to explore and lots of other diversions nearby for family outings
